title: Facebook and Twitter CEOs to testify before Congress in November on how they handled the election
text: Shortly after voting to move forward with a pair of subpoenas, the Senate Judiciary Committee has reached an agreement that will see the CEOs of two major social platforms testify voluntarily in November. The hearing will be the second major congressional appearance by tech CEOs arranged this month.

title: U.S. investigators may file antitrust charges against Facebook as soon as November: Washington Post
text: Federal and state investigators in the United States are expected to file antitrust charges against social media company Facebook Inc as soon as November, the Washington Post reported on Friday, citing four people familiar with the matter.

title: Sen. Graham says he is getting close to a 'voluntary agreement' for big tech CEOs to testify
text: Sen. Lindsey Graham is getting close to a voluntary agreement to have Jack Dorsey and Mark Zuckerberg to testify before the Judiciary Committee after the election. Ylan Mui joins 'Closing Bell' to discuss.

title: Former FTC Commissioner Mozelle Thompson on potential Facebook antitrust probe
